trend_summary: 2000-2020 imagery shows largely stable residential quarters in the north-west while forest has been progressively cleared for quarries and spoil heaps in the centre and east. New haul roads, ponds and industrial pads accompany extraction. Only limited infill housing appears; shoreline and waterways stay mostly unchanged.
notable_changes: Large beige quarry pits emerge and expand in the central-eastern sector.
Progressive forest loss around new extraction zones and access corridors.
Two rectangular blue settling ponds appear and grow south of the quarry.
New curvilinear haul roads connect pits to the existing highway grid.
Minor residential and commercial infill inside the north-western urban block.
